I"<h1 id="ghost-rider-tims-engineering-calculators">Ghost Rider Tim’s Engineering Calculators</h1>

<p>The following Excel Spreadsheets were developed by our team for our own engineering work. We are open-sourcing these calculators for public use to enable others to design safe, and reliable systems. <strong>Please note that these calculators come with reccomended reading resources, that we HIGHLY reccomend you review before using these calculators.</strong></p>

<p><a href="/calculators/bolt_calculator_v1-1.xlsx">Bolted Joint Calculator</a> <i class="fa-brands fa-creative-commons"></i></p>

<p><a href="/calculators/slips_and_fits_v1-1.xlsx">Slip + Interference Fits</a> <i class="fa-brands fa-creative-commons"></i></p>

<p><img src="/Licence%20to%20Fab%20Logos/biker_gang_logos/GhostRiderTIMv2.png" width="40%" /></p>

<h1 id="engineering-resources">Engineering Resources</h1>

<p>The following are resources for general engineering that we compiled for our work. Please note that we only publish resources which are freely avaliable online or have been open-sourced. For books that don’t have PDFs linked you will likely have to purchase them, or gain access through your local/university library.</p>

<h2 id="safety">Safety</h2>

<p><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1tSw06zePS63g3Wz79YGt5xviOAI2fiKx/view?usp=share_link">The FAA’s ACCEPTABLE METHODS, TECHNIQUES, AND PRACTICES—AIRCRAFT INSPECTION AND REPAIR (Section 7, Safety Wire Methods)</a></p>

<p><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1W8uPz_L5l6Vr9hztAcji3yXbUoJ1Thde/view?usp=sharing">The US DoT NHSTA’s Failure Mode Analysis for Hydrogen Vehicles</a></p>

<p><a href="https://h2tools.org">H2 Tools Resources on Hydrogen Safety</a></p>

<p><a href="https://h2tools.org/fuel-cell-codes-and-standards?search_api_fulltext=">Hydrogen Codes + Standards Searchable Database</a></p>

